i-MSCP  - HowTo Install On Debian
=================================

Table of Content
================

1) Version Info
2) Requirements
3) Introduction
4) Installation
5) Update
6) Uninstall
7) Credits

1)  Version Info
----------------

i-MSCP Version:  1.1.15
Maintainer:      i-MSCP Team
Homepage:        http://www.i-mscp.net
Distros:         Debian Squeeze, Wheezy (recommended), Jessie

2)  Requirements
----------------

 - 1 GHz or faster 32-bit (x86) or 64-bit (x64) processor
 - 1024 MiB RAM minimum - For heavily loaded servers or high flow is recommended at least 8 GiB
 - 2 GiB of available hard disk space (only for i-MSCP and related services)
 - Internet Access (100 Mbits/s recommended)
 - A file system supporting extended attributes (eg. immutable flag) such as ext2, ext3, ext4 and reiserfs*.

* See http://wiki.i-mscp.net/doku.php?id=start:howto:reiserfs

All packages are listed in ./docs/Ubuntu/packages-<codename>.xml

3)  Introduction
----------------

i-MSCP delivers a complete hosting automation appliance by offering significant security, total-cost-of-ownership, and
performance advantages over competing commercial solutions.

With i-MSCP you can configure your server and applications, create user with domains with a few point-and-click
operations that take less than a minute. There is no limit to the number of resellers, users and domains that can be
created. The core of i-MSCP are 3 easy-to-use, web-based control panels. i-MSCP provides graphic user interfaces for the
administrators, resellers and users.

4)  Installation
----------------

Make sure you are logged in as root:

1. Install the required packages

	# apt-get update && apt-get install tasksel
	# tasksel install standard

2.  Download and untar or unzip the distribution files to a secure directory

	# cd /usr/local/src
	# wget https://github.com/i-MSCP/imscp/archive/1.1.15.tar.gz
	# tar xzf imscp-1.1.15.tar.gz

3.  Change to the newly created directory

	# cd imscp-1.1.15

4.  Run the imscp-autoinstall script

	# perl ./imscp-autoinstall -d

5.  Install i-MSCP step-by-step

	If you get no error, all went good; if you get one, look at http://i-mscp.net to solve the problem.

6)  Update
----------

Make sure you are logged in as root and MySQL is running.

1.  Download and untar the distribution files to a secure directory

	# cd /usr/local/src
	# wget https://github.com/i-MSCP/imscp/archive/1.1.15.tar.gz
	# tar xzf imscp-1.1.15.tar.gz

2. Change to the newly created directory

	# cd imscp-1.1.15

3.  Update by running the imscp-autoinstall script

	# perl imscp-autoinstall -d

4.  Update i-MSCP step-by-step

	If you get no error, all went good; if you get one, look at http://i-mscp.net to solve the problem.

6)  Uninstall
-------------

Make sure you are logged in as root and MySQL is running.

1.  Change into the engine directory

	# cd /var/www/imscp/engine/setup

2.  Start the uninstall script

	# perl imscp-uninstall

3.  Clean up your system

